A startup called Tamr launched on Monday with technology geared to help companies organize the often sloppy and massive amounts of data that plug up their infrastructure .

The company - which was founded in 2013 by database expert Michael Stonebraker and longtime business partner Andy Palmer -  hopes to merge machine learning with human insight in order to generate quicker and more accurate data analysis .
Tamr has raised $ 16 million in venture capital from Google Ventures and New Enterprise Associates .
The machine - learning algorithms and software can do the dirty work of organizing messy data sets that would otherwise take a person thousands of hours to do the same , Palmer said .
